    "prose_paragraphs": [
      "A deliberate color. WOODLAND GREEN works on craftsman, traditional, and cottage-style elevations where the roof is meant to grow out of the landscape. The granule blend uses dark olive and brown accents to keep the surface visually warm.",
      "Atlas keeps the green saturation deliberately low so the color reads as natural rather than artificial. The result is a roof that ages gracefully without ever pulling into 'AstroTurf' territory.",
      "Works best on craftsman, traditional, and rustic-cottage builds. Stays clear of contemporary all-white elevations where the green can read as period-incorrect."
